Gaming Portal

Gaming Portal (Playwing) is a mobile store service that provides premium games for Android devices.

The games are without ads or in-app purchases! The service is available on one-time and Auto-renewal option.

Gaming Portal (Playwing) has a catalogue of more than 250 premium games, which include top rated games like Rayman, Prince of Persia, Cut the Rope, Raiden Legacy, Assassins Creed, Lara Croft Relic Run, Smurfs Epic Run and lots more.


Now you can spend as many hours as you want enjoying the very best collection of games on your phone.


To cap it all, if you subscribe to the Gaming Portal (Playwing) store through Glo, you actually pay a much lower price, compared to buying these games separately elsewhere.


So how do you get on the fun train?

Simply send by SMS the word SUB PLAYWING to 55883 (Toll Free), or dial *577#. You will receive a link to Gaming Portal Service http://store.playwing.com/


Subscription cost

N30 only for a day (2 Games download per day). Data charges apply.

The same is available on both one-time and auto-renewal mode.


If you wish to unsubscribe from Playwing Gaming Portal, all you need to do is send by SMS UNSUB Game to 577 or Dial *577# (Toll Free).


Gaming Portal is available to both Prepaid and Postpaid customers.


Now let your games begin!!!

Got Questions?

What is Playwing Premium?

Playwing Premium is a subscription service which is automatically renewed every day unless you unsubscribe when you subscribe to AUTO RENEWAL option. You can terminate your subscription whenever you want only by entering in your personal menu on store.playwing.com (icon at top right of the display) and clicking on Leave my Playwing Premium link. Depending on your mobile operator, you may terminate your subscription by sending a SMS.

Is it safe to download games from Playwing store?

Yes, all Playwing games are 100% safe for your handset and your personal data.

Auto renewal subscription to playwing via Glo

  • Direct subscription to SDP: Send GAME to 577
  • From USSD: Dial. *577# and choose game Portal
  • Web channel: Send Game to 55883 and you will receive an SMS. With a link as below as http://glo-nga.telenity.com/landing/pw/lp?cid=5ed795c256b03

  • If you are on Glo 3G/4G network, you will see the landing page, please tick in Im top gamer and then click on SUBSCRIBE button.



    If you are using another internet source, you will be required to supply your phone number with the preceeding 0 as +234 is already supplied then click SUBSCRIBE

  • You will be redirected to the landing page. Click on Subscribe
  • As message requesting confirmation will be displayed: Dear user, you are subscribing Playwing day, if you dont reply, system will not deduct rent 30.00 NGN from your balance. 0. Subscribe.
  • Respond by replying 0 You will receive this SMS from 577: You have successfully subscribed to GAME AUTO and it takes effect at 2020-06-18 09:17:50. To unsubscribe send unsub game to 577 or dial *577#
  • You will also receive an SMS from Playwing as follows: Welcome to Playwing! To enjoy your games go to: www.store.playwing.com

  • Click on the url in the SMS or enter the url into your browser.


How can I know how many remaining games I have from my subscription to Playwing premium?

Just access to your personal menu and you can check the number of games left. Normally, in the homepage you can read a message on top which advises you about how many remaining games you have.

One time subscription to Playwing via Glo

  • Direct subscription to SDP: Send GAME ONETIME to 577
  • From dial: *577# and choose game Portal
  • Web channel: Send Game to 55883 and you will receive an SMS. With a link as below as http://glo-nga.telenity.com/landing/pw/lp?cid=5ed795c256b03

  • If you are on Glo 3G/4G network, you will see the landing page, please tick in Im a casual gamer and then click on SUBSCRIBE button.

    If you are using another internet source, you will be required to supply your phone number with the preceeding 0 as +234 is already supplied then click SUBSCRIBE

  • You will be redirected to the landing page. Click on Subscribe
  • As message requesting confirmation will be displayed: Dear user, you are subscribing Playwing day, if you dont reply, system will not deduct rent 30.00 NGN from your balance. 0. Subscribe.
  • Respond by replying 0
    You will receive this SMS from 577: You have successfully subscribed to GAME ONETIME and it takes effect at 2020-06-11 08:20:41. To unsubscribe send unsub UNSUB PLAYWING to 55883 or dial *577#
  • You will also receive an SMS from Playwing as follows: Welcome to Playwing! To enjoy your games go to: www.store.playwing.com

  • Click on the url in the SMS or enter the url into your browser.

I am subscribed to Playwing premium, if I unsubscribe, will I lose my games?

No, downloaded games from Playwing store are for users to keep (not a renting model). Even as long as you are subscribed, you are able to re-download all games you bought within the last 14 days: go to personal menu and find them on My Downloads section. If you would like to re-download previous games, just contact us

Unsubscribing

A. How can I terminate my subscription to Playwing Premium?

Playwing Premium is a subscription service which is automatically renewed every day unless you unsubscribe. You can terminate your subscription whenever you want only by entering in your personal menu on store.playwing.com (icon at top right of the display) and clicking on Leave my Playwing Premium link. Depending on your mobile operator, you may terminate your subscription by sending a SMS.


B. How to unsubscribe?

Unsubscription for auto renewal model:

  • Direct subscription to SDP: Send and SMS with UNSUB GAME to 577
  • Or from dial: *577# and choose unsubscribe

Unsubscription for one time model:

  • Direct subscription to SDP: Send and SMS with UNSUB GAME ONETIME to 577
  • Or from dial: *577# and choose unsubscribe
  • You will receive instruction with url to un-subscribe e.g Simply click link www.store.playwing.com/myaccount
  • Click on Leave my Playwing Premium
  • A message requesting confirmation for unsubscription will be displayed, please click on Yes

  • You will receive an SMS like below: Dear customer, you have successfully unsubscribed from Playwing . Thank you

Once I subscribed to Playwing premium, if I didnt download games along one week or day, will I lose those games?

Not at all. You will accumulate those games until you want to spend them.

Where can I download my games?

To download, install and enjoy your games, you should simple access to our homepage store.playwing.com and click on Download buttons. You are able to browse our whole catalogue on the main menu (searching by title or category). For games over 50 Mb we strongly recommend downloading from WIFI connection (to avoid high 3G mobile data consumption) and store them in a SD card.

The mobile site does not detect my account and my subscription to Playwing premium

Check your 3G or WIFI connection is working properly. If so, and this issue persists, please contact us indicating your issue, phone number, mobile operator and handset.

I already downloaded one game but I cannot install it on my handset, what is happening?

First of all, make sure that you have permission to install apps from different stores to Google Play: in your device, go to settings / Security / Device Administration and enable Unknown Sources Allow installation of apps from unknown sources. In addition, you might check if you have enough space in your storage. If this issue persists, dont hesitate to contact us

Customer care Playwing contact information

Email: support@playwing.com

Moreover, there is a contact form, in My account section, through which users can contact Playwing store.playwing.com/my_account

Job Applicant Privacy Notice

Introduction

In this Recruitment Notice, Globacom, we, our and us refer to Globacom Limited, incorporated under the laws of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, with its registered office at Mike Adenuga Towers, 1 Mike Adenuga Close, Off Adeola Odeku Street, Victoria Island, Lagos. We are committed to the fair, transparent, and lawful processing of your personal data in accordance with the Nigeria Data Protection Act (NDPA), and to safeguarding your privacy in every step of our recruitment process.

Definitions

Personal Data Any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person, including but not limited to names, contact details, identification numbers, education history, and employment information.
Sensitive Personal Data Special categories of data such as health, race or ethnic origin, religious beliefs, trade union membership, biometric data, or criminal records.
Data Subject A natural person whose personal data is being processed in this case, a job applicant.
Processing Any operation performed on personal data (collection, storage, use, disclosure, deletion) whether automated or not.
Third Party Any person or entity other than the data subject, the data controller, or those authorized to process data under the controllers direct authority.

Scope

This notice applies to all individuals applying for employment at Globacom, whether through our official careers portal, third-party platforms, or recruitment agencies.

Types of Data Collected

  • Bio data: Full name, date of birth, gender, etc.
  • Contact information: phone number, email, address.
  • Academic and professional qualifications, employment history and references, CVs, certificates, identification documents, background checks, and any other information relevant to evaluating your application.

Lawful Basis for Processing

Your personal data is processed on one or more lawful bases including: performance of a contract/pre-contractual obligations, legal obligations, consent (for sensitive personal data or retention for future roles), and legitimate interests (improving recruitment, diversity, fraud prevention). You may withdraw consent at any time where processing relied on consent.

Data Collection Methods

We collect data via our online application platform, email submissions, third-party recruitment agencies, Google Forms, and in-person or virtual interviews and assessments.

Data Use Purpose

We use your personal data to process applications, assess qualifications, conduct interviews and background checks, contact you about application status, and retain information for future recruitment where you consent.

Data Sharing & Disclosure

Personal data may be shared with internal HR and recruitment teams, third-party service providers under NDPA-compliant agreements, regulatory authorities where required, and affiliated companies for group-level recruitment purposes.

Data Retention

Personal data is kept, reviewed periodically and destroyed in line with law, the purpose it was obtained for, contract terms, statutory requirements, or upon a valid deletion request where no investigation or statutory restriction applies.

Your Rights

  • Right to request and access Personal Data held about you (including a common electronic format where structured).
  • Right to information on personal data collected and stored.
  • Right to object or request restriction, rectification, or deletion (subject to legal limitations).
  • Right to data portability.
  • Right to object to automated decision making/profiling.
  • Right to opt out of marketing and unsolicited messages.
  • Right to lodge a complaint with the Nigeria Data Protection Commission (NDPC).

Data Security & Breach Response

We use industry-standard technical and organisational measures (encryption at rest, access controls, security audit logging, physical security) to protect personal data. In case of a breach, we will contain, investigate, notify affected applicants and the NDPC within 72 hours (where required), and provide guidance to affected individuals.

Third Parties & Cross-Border Transfers

We may disclose data to service providers, law enforcement, regulators, or in corporate transactions. Cross-border transfers occur only with appropriate safeguards such as NDPC-approved instruments (SCCs, BCRs), and only when adequate protections are in place.

Changes to this Notice

Globacom may update this Recruitment Notice periodically to reflect legal, regulatory, or operational changes. Significant changes will be notified via our website or email.

Contact Information

Data Protection Officer

Globacom Limited

Email: dpo.globacom@gloworld.com

NDPC (for complaints): info@ndpc.gov.ng Phone: +234 (0) 916 061 5551

Privacy & Cookies Consent

Your privacy is very important to us and we only process your personal information to enhance your experience. Continuing to use this platform indicates your consent to the processing of your personal information by Globacom in accordance with NDPA. We use cookies for tracking, analytics, and content delivery from other sites.
